<% if @current_visitor %>

  <p>The session will reset after you logout.</p>
  <p>Registered email: <%= @current_visitor[:email] %> </p>
  <p><%= pluralize(@total, "Visitor") %> signed up.</p>

  <br>

  <p>Source code available <%= link_to 'here', "https://github.com/JuzerShakir/Session-CookieStore", target: :_blank %>.</p>
  <p>My Next <%= link_to 'project', "", target: :_blank %>.</p>

<% else %>

  <h2>Hey Devs, Welcome to my First Portfolio</h2>
  <p>This project is a demonstration of how to implement a session on Rails using the default session store, the <i>'CookieStore'</i>.</p>

  <p>To see this in action, <%= link_to "Sign Up", :new_visitor %> with an email (it could be any as long as its in valid email format) and password (mimimum of 6 characters).</p>

  <p>After signing up, you will be redirected to this page but now you will <b>no longer be able to see this content until you sign out.</b></p>

  <br>

  <p><%= pluralize(@total, "Visitor") %> already signed up.</p>

<% end %>
